domosaics.ui.io.menureader
Class MenuEntry

java.lang.Object
  domosaics.ui.io.menureader.MenuEntry

public class MenuEntry
extends java.lang.Object

Class MenuEntry represents a JComponent within a JMenu. This could for example be a JMenuBar, Menu, MenuItem, JSeparator or JCheckboxItem. For a list of all supported menu item types see enumeration class MenuEntryType.

A MenuEntry can hold a name, shortcut, tooltip, image and action.

To add new types of menu entry do the following:
1. add the new type to MenuEntryType.
2. Extend the create(MenuActionManager) method, so that the correct JComponent for the new type is returned.
3. Use the new type in the menu XML format
4. Add an entry for the new type in the menu parser MenuReader

Author:
Andreas Held
